# Cursor Rules

## Communication & Workflow
- **Always ask clarifying questions** before starting any coding task
- **ALWAYS Wait for user confirmation** before implementing code changes
- **Break down complex tasks** into smaller, confirmable steps
- **Explain your approach** and reasoning before proceeding
- **Provide context** for why certain decisions are made

## Code Quality & Standards
- **Follow existing code patterns** in the project
- **Maintain consistency** with the current codebase style
- **Add proper error handling** with user-friendly error messages
- **Include necessary imports** and dependencies
- **Add TypeScript types** where applicable

## Testing & Validation
- **Test edge cases** and error scenarios
- **Validate inputs** and handle invalid data gracefully
- **Ensure backward compatibility** when making changes
- **Check for linting errors** and fix them

## Documentation & Comments
- **Add clear comments** for complex logic
- **Update relevant documentation** when making changes
- **Explain non-obvious decisions** in code comments

## Performance & UX
- **Prioritize user experience** in all decisions
- **Consider performance implications** of changes
- **Implement graceful degradation** when possible
- **Provide loading states** and user feedback

## Security & Best Practices
- **Follow security best practices** for API endpoints
- **Validate and sanitize inputs** appropriately
- **Use environment variables** for sensitive configuration
- **Implement proper authentication** checks where needed
